labels.label:
This is the ETL pipeline for a tracking project.
Please ensure to do the following as instructed in the project README: * Add and enable the default DistributedMapCacheServer Controller Service * Enable all the remaining Controller Services * Add the PutS3Object processor credentials

This process group contains the processors that generate the flows for the ETL pipeline. These processors only have to run once and never again for this exercise.
Wait-Notify logic was added to ensure that the Druid-Kafka supervisor schema is first posted on Druid so that it can start monitoring the Kafka topic.
The InvokeHHTP processor posts the configured Druid Kafka ingestion spec to Druid. This let druid run real time jobs that will pull data from Kafka topic into druid real-time nodes for segmenting.
